IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO PROVIDE THE COMPREHENSIVE EDUCATION AND TRAINING NECESSARY TO PREPARE STUDENTS FOR EMPLOYMENT AND ADVANCEMENT IN A VARIETY OF TECHNICAL FIELDS.
IRS990.MissionDesc: RANKEN TECHNICAL COLLEGE IS A PRIVATE, NON-PROFIT, DEGREE-GRANTING INSTITUTION OF HIGHER LEARNING WHOSE PRIMARY MISSION IS TO PROVIDE THE COMPREHENSIVE EDUCATION AND TRAINING NECESSARY TO PREPARE STUDENTS FOR EMPLOYMENT AND ADVANCEMENT IN A VARIETY OF TECHNICAL FIELDS.
IRS990.Desc: 1,900 STUDENTS SERVED IN ASSOCIATED DEGREE PROGRAMS IN THIRTY-SIX TECHNICAL FIELDS AND BACHELOR OF SCIENCE DEGREES IN ARCHITECTURAL TECHNOLOGY STUDIES AND APPLIED MANAGEMENT. 600 STUDENTS SERVED IN CONTINUING EDUCATION PROGRAMS WITH CERTIFICATE GRANTING IN THIRTY SIX AREAS. 1,800 STUDENTS SERVED IN INDUSTRIAL TRAINING PROGRAMS. RANKEN TECHNICAL COLLEGE IS A PRIVATE, NON-PROFIT INSTITUTION OF HIGHER EDUCATION. RICH WITH HISTORY, RANKEN HAS PROVIDED STUDENTS WITH TOP QUALITY EDUCATIONAL PROGRAMS FOR NEARLY 100 YEARS. RANKEN'S STATE-OF-THE-ART EQUIPMENT AND FACILITIES AND CAMPUS ARE CONTINUALLY UPDATED TO PROVIDE STUDENTS EXPOSURE TO CUTTING-EDGE TECHNOLOGY. THROUGH DAY AND CONTINUING EDUCATION PROGRAMS, RANKEN STUDENTS ARE TRAINED TO ENTER OVER 100 PROFESSIONAL FIELDS. EACH PROGRAM FEATURES: - A COMBINATION OF TECHNICAL STUDIES, GENERAL EDUCATION AND PROFESSIONALISM - HANDS-ON EXPERIENCE IN A VARIETY OF TECHNICAL FIELDS - INVOLVED AND EXPERIENCED FACULTY - LIFETIME JOB PLACEMENT RANKEN'S GREAT REPUTATION AMONG BUSINESS AND INDUSTRY HELPS STUDENTS FIND JOBS. OUR GRADUATES EACH HAVE EXPOSURE TO AN AVERAGE OF FIVE TO SEVEN JOB OPPORTUNITIES. TO ENSURE THE REAL-WORLD RELEVANCE OF WHAT WE TEACH, TECHNICAL ADVISORY COMMITTEES MADE UP OF INDUSTRY REPRESENTATIVES HELP GUIDE AND SHAP PROGRAM CURRICULUM. SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: USE OF ENDOWMENT FUNDS: THE LISTED FUNDS WILL BE USED FOR SCHOLARSHIPS, EDUCATIONAL EQUIPMENT AND TECHNOLOGY PURCHASES, CAMPUS RENOVATION, STUDENT RESIDENCE HALL CAPITAL EXPENDITURES, AND OTHER STUDENT FINANCIAL AID.

FIN 48: MANAGEMENT HAS EVALUATED THEIR INCOME TAX POSITIONS UNDER THE GUIDANCE INCLUDED IN ASC 740. BASED ON THEIR REVIEW, MANAGEMENT HAS NOT IDENTIFIED ANY MATERIAL UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS TO BE RECORDED OR DISCLOSED IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.
THE COLLEGE HAS PUBLICIZED ITS RACIALLY NONDISCRIMINATORY POLICY THROUGH ITS WEBSITE & SOCIAL MEDIA, IN COLLEGE BROCHURES, AND IN E-MAILS TO STUDENTS AND EMPLOYEES.

FINANCIAL AID OR ASSISTANCE FROM GOVERNMENTAL AGENCY: THE ORGANIZATION RECEIVES A TRIO STUDENT SUPPORT SERVICES GRANT FROM THE U.S DEPARTMENT OF EDUCATION AND NSF STEM AND PIPELINE GRANTS TO FURTHER TECHNICAL EDUCATION EXPOSURE.

GrantsOtherAsstToIndivInUSGrp.GrantTypeTxt: MO DEPT OF LABOR AND RELATIONS DIV OF EMPLOYMENT

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: USE OF GRANT FUNDS: THE COLLEGE HAS IN PLACE ASSURANCES/SAFEGUARDS THAT INCLUDE GENERALLY ACCEPTED ACCOUNTING STANDARDS, AND ADDITIONAL FISCAL PROCEDURES FOR THE SUBMISSION AND APPROVAL OF INVOICES FOR THE PROPER USE OF GRANT FUNDS. FOR EXPENDITURES THAT PROVIDE SPECIFIC ASSISTANCE TO INDIVIDUALS (IN THE FORM OF SCHOLARSHIPS AND OTHER FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE TO PAY FOR TUITION, SUPPLIES AND FEES), THE COLLEGE'S FINANCIAL AID OFFICE KEEPS COMPLETE AND ACCURATE INFORMATION ON EACH INDIVIDUAL RECIPIENT THAT INCLUDES DATA ON ELIGIBILITY, ACADEMIC PERFORMANCE AND AMOUNT OF FUNDS AWARDED/DISBURSED. FOR EXPENDITURES IN SUPPORT OF PROGRAMMATIC ACTIVITIES PROGRAM MANAGERS MUST REVIEW EXPENDITURE REQUESTS TO ENSURE THAT EACH IS AN APPROPRIATE EXPENDITURE FOR APPROVED ACTIVITIES IN THE APPROVED BUDGET FOR THE GRANT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: SCHEDULE K, PART IV, LINE 1C, COLUMN B
FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FORM 990 REVIEW PROCESS: THE PRESIDENT AND CHIEF FINANCIAL OFFICER OF THE ORGANIZATION CONDUCT A REVIEW OF THE FORM 990 PRIOR TO FINALIZING THE FORM. AFTER THE FORM 990 HAS BEEN FINALIZED, A COPY IS PROVIDED TO VOTING MEMBERS OF THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES PRIOR TO FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COMPLIANCE WITH CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY: BOARD OF TRUSTEE MEMBERS ARE REQUIRED TO COMPLETE A CONFLICT OF INTEREST DISCLOSURE QUESTIONNAIRE TO IDENTIFY POTENTIAL CONFLICTS OF INTEREST THAT A MEMBER MAY HAVE. IF A CONFLICT IS DISCLOSED, THE CHAIRMEN AND THE BOARD TRUSTEE WOULD DISCUSS THE SITUATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ADDITIONAL DOCUMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC: THE ORGANIZATION DOES MAKE ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: PROCESS FOR DETERMINING COMPENSATION: OUTSIDE COMPARATIVE SALARY/COMPENSATION INFORMATION IS COMPILED BY THE ORGANIZATION'S HUMAN RESOURCES DEPARTMENT AND REPORTED TO THE AUDIT AND COMPENSATION COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD. THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES USES THIS DATA IN DETERMINING COMPENSATION FOR THE PRESIDENT AND OTHER OFFICERS OF THE ORGANIZATION. THE COMMITTEE MET IN MAY 2023 AND REVIEWED A SALARY SURVEY AND THEN MADE COMPENSATION RECOMMENDATIONS TO THE FULL BOARD.
